uml4iot.GenericStateMachine.core

Class Transition

  • java.lang.Object
    • uml4iot.GenericStateMachine.core.Transition

  • public abstract class Transition
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a transition of a state, that is triggered to go to the next state. Transitions are added to states and check for events that triggers them

    • Constructor Detail

      • Transition

        public Transition(State fromState,
                  State toState,
                  boolean fork,
                  boolean join,
                  boolean completion)
        Complex constructor of the transition.
        Parameters:
        fromState - The source state
        toState - The target state
        fork - True if the transition forks the state machine to have multiple target states
        join - True if there is another branch that must be completed before this transition completes
        completion - True if the transition is completion, ie it does'nt require an event to trigger

      • Transition

        public Transition(State fromState,
                  State toState)
        Simpler constructor of the transition, only source and target states are required
        Parameters:
        fromState - The source state
        toState - The target state

    • Method Detail

      • setCompletion

        public Transition setCompletion()
        Builder method to activate completion. When this is called, transition will not require an event to trigger
        Returns:
        the current instance

      • setFork

        public Transition setFork()
        Builder method to activate fork When this is called, transition will enable forking, ie 2 states will be activated in parallel. If fork is enabled, branchInitState must be called with the appropriate init state (branch init state)
        Returns:
        the current instance

      • setJoin

        public Transition setJoin()
        Builder method to enable join When this is called, transition will wait for forks to complete before continuing to the next state
        Returns:
        the current instance

      • hasFork

        public boolean hasFork()
        Getter method for checking if transition has fork enabled
        Returns:
        true if transition has fork enabled else false

      • hasJoin

        public boolean hasJoin()
        Getter method for checking if transition has join enabled
        Returns:
        true if transition has join enabled, else false

      • setBranchInitState

        public void setBranchInitState(State st)
        If fork is enabled (by setFork()) this method must be called with the branch init state

      • isCompletion

        public boolean isCompletion()
        Getter method for checking if transition has completion enabled
        Returns:
        true if completion is enabled, else false

      • trigger

        protected abstract boolean trigger(SMReception smr)
        This method is called from the state machine to check if the transition is trigger by an event.
        Parameters:
        smr - current event for checking if this transition triggers
        Returns:
        true if the event trigger change of state, else false

      • effect

        protected abstract void effect()
        A hook to add functionality when a transition is triggered. It is called after the State.exit() method
